    • Method Detail

      • init

        void init(Map<String,String> engineConfigurationProperties)
        Invoked once, after processor has been created. This method is invoked only once and before any processing is done and should be used to initialize processor.
        Parameters:
        engineConfigurationProperties - configuration properties supplied to engine at startup

      • preProcessDataLine

        String[] preProcessDataLine(String[] parsedDataLine,
                          Map<String,String> globalAttributes)
        Invoked once per feed line before that line is passed further for processing (just after line has been read from file). Must be fast - since it will be invoked once per every line in feed.

        It is very important to keep this method fast because it is executed once per every row in input feed files.

        Parameters:
        parsedDataLine - parsed data row read from file
        globalAttributes - global attributes available at the moment when row is being parsed. It is possible to modify these attributes in this method and modified or newly created attributes will be available further down the processing chain.
        Returns:
        modified data. Must be the same length as passed array
